To find number of digits -> Math.log10(num) + 1

To split the numbers ->  while(num > 0) { rem = num % 10; num = num / 10; }

To reverse digits of a num -> while(num > 0) { rem = num % 10; num = num / 10; revnum = revnum*10 + rem; }

To convert string to chararray -> str.toCharArray()

To print the converted char array -> System.out.println(Arrays.toString(str.toCharArray()));

To Concate same array twice
System.arraycopy(source_arr,src_pos,dest_arr,dest_pos,length)

To sort an array
Arrays.sort(<array name>);

to sort an  array in reverse order
Arrays.sort(arr , Collections.reverseOrder());

to sort a list of integers
Collections.sort(list);

to sort a list in reverse order
Collections.sort(list , collections.reverseOrder());